        but return right away with id == None. The existance of this method is explained by the fact that GoGrid assigns id to a node only few minutes after creation.
        Parameters:
        name - String with a name for this new node (required) (:type name: ``str``)
        size - The size of resources allocated to this node . (required) (:type size: :class:`NodeSize`)
        image - OS Image to boot on node. (required) (:type image: :class:`NodeImage`)
        ex_description - Description of a Node (:type ex_description: ``str``)
        ex_ip - Public IP address to use for a Node. If not specified, first available IP address will be picked (:type ex_ip: ``str``)
